        "title": "Why would aFile.toURI().toString() on linux have a single slash?",
        "body": "<p>What is the deal with Java's bizarre file protocol handling?\nI mean on windows UNC path's get turned into 5 slashes, and I get why that happens, but on linux an absolute path gets turned into <code>file:/local/path/to/file<\/code> \nShouldn't that have three slashes?\nI'm assuming the authors of Java aren't incompetent, so is there an explanation for why that's acceptable?<\/p>\n",
